THIS IS 30 🖤 Words cannot describe how grateful I am to have the most incredible people in my life. I’ve always looked forward to being 30 in hopes that I’d have everything figured out, and although I’m forever learning and growing, I’m still so proud of myself for the woman I’ve become from both my wins and my mistakes. I wouldn’t be able to live without the amazing human beings that have stuck by my side. 

I don’t always write novels or get mushy but I LOVE YOU ALL, and thank you for making this the best birthday yet. 😭🖤

#flirty30

Feeling grateful to be able to move my body for a cause that touches so close to home. 💗

I do it for my family members that have been effected by cancer, for the genetic mutation I have that puts me at a higher risk for this awful disease, for my mental health so I can continue to support my friends and family, and to live a long, functional life to create the best memories that I’ll never forget. Everyone has their reasons for leading a healthy lifestyle, and these are my biggest drivers. I am grateful to be surrounded by people who support me and stay active alongside me. 🫀

Pls also enjoy pup pics for serotonin. The end 🐶
Mountain bbs. 🏔️ Spending more time enjoying life with the people that make me happy. 🖤
To more mirror pics, good doggos, quality time with my favorite people, and running more miles in 2024. 💓
